The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, for statistical downscaling of climate variables. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), with a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-scale input channels, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.DL).
